item.title: Reply to 'How to create a .py file for Google App Engine?' on stackoverflow at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1866147/how-to-create-a-py-file-for-google-app-engine:
item.author: hello@roytang.net (Roy Tang)
item.description:
Reply to 'How to create a .py file for Google App Engine?' on stackoverflow at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1866147/how-to-create-a-py-file-for-google-app-engine:

You will need a better editor than Notepad. With Notepad, use Save As…, and type “helloworld.py” in the dialog, including quotes so that the file extension is .py instead of .txt

item.title: Reply to 'Apache POI - error in reading excel file' on stackoverflow at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1859454/apache-poi-error-in-reading-excel-file:
item.author: hello@roytang.net (Roy Tang)
item.description:
Reply to 'Apache POI - error in reading excel file' on stackoverflow at https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1859454/apache-poi-error-in-reading-excel-file:

POI probably has a dependency on log4j. Just include the log4j jar in your classpath.
